cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM

The paper deals with connectivity estimation in LTE networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves analyzing control traffic and estimating data rates, which are topics related to security and information theory, respectively. Hence, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are also likely categories. The paper proposes a mechanism for decision-making in cyber-physical systems, which involves the integration of hardware and software components. Therefore, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category. Finally, the paper involves the use of real-life LTE networks and load generators, which are topics related to multimedia and human-computer interaction. Hence, cs.MM (Multimedia) is a less likely but still possible category.
